http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/Temple-elephant-sent-to-rejuvenation-camp/article13984948.ece

Sri Dhandayuthapaniswamy temple administration here on Wednesday sent the temple elephant Kasturi to rejuvenation camp at Mettupalayam on Wednesday.After special pujas, the 49-year-old elephant, weighing 4,600 kg, boarded the lorry on Wednesday morning. Officials from HR&CE, Forest and Revenue Departments were present.Earlier, veterinary doctors checked the health condition of Kasturi. She was fit to travel, said veterinary doctor Rajendran.Kasturi had won the first prize in a competition held in the previous camp, the officials recalled.